The paper uses information theory to derive lower bounds and applies noisy binary search, which are techniques commonly used in the subfield of information theory (cs.IT) and algorithms (cs.DS). The problem of determining a set of indistinguishable integers falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Additionally, the use of queries and comparisons suggests a potential application in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
